reviewText: Adult audience gut-busting humor to offend everyone with realism and perspective. Highly recommended for attitude adjustment and mindless entertainment value.

If you like Bill Maher, you will love DL Hughley.

I will watch anything with DL, even if it is just an interview.  He is funny of course, but his social commentary is needed.  The fact that he can make you laugh your butt off while speaking truth, logic, and reason is just genius.
This video is great.

DL Hughley is a comical genius.
He has the timing of one of those expensive grandfather clocks or a rolex.
Impeccable , and worth listening to on repeat, even after i'm dead i'm gonna have some 22 inch speakers on either side of my grave to play DL Hughley.

Aint no thang a but a chicken wang.

This had me cracking up throughout the entire thing! DL is quite intelligent and aware of current events and he makes it quite evident in his comedy. We need more comedians who can find humor in everyday life and who also enlighten the audience about politics, religion, and the like. This is absolutely great and well-worth the money!

Absolutely hilarious. I saw the special several times on HBO and decided I should own it. I was already in love with it, but I saw the deleted scenes and almost died! I'm surprised they were deleted in the first place because I couldn't stop laughing.

I thought his previous show on HBO a few years ago was hilarious, but this one topped it. Having seen DL's bit on Comic View years ago, I never thought he was very funny. His part in the Kings of Comedy was so so, to me. His TV show was good, but his last 2 HBO Specials have convinced me that this man is brilliant. His appearances on Bill Maher's show on HBO shows a sample of his comedy and intelligence (yes, he's intelligent along with being funny), but this show is over the top funny. I've encouraged co-workers to watch the show and/or buy the DVD every chance I've gotten.
The funniest guy in showbiz! Hands down! Never laughed so much watching a stand up comic. So real so funny so on point!

Didn't think the show was funny at all.  I saw him on Bill Maher one time a few years back and he was arguing about "slavery" and of course focusing on the 260 years of slavery in the USA and screamed that black people were not selling or buying slaves in America.  I haven't watched that show since either.  According to the 1860 Census Free Black People in the USA at the time owned more working black slaves per capita than white people.  So he was wrong then too.  And not funny as well..
